    <passage>
      <offset>62</offset>
      <infon key="type">body</infon>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">2</infon>
        <offset>62</offset>
        <text>Redfield noted the similarity between the average nitrogen-to-phosphorus ratio in plankton (N:P = 16 by atoms) and in deep oceanic waters (N:P = 15; refs 1, 2).
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">3</infon>
        <offset>223</offset>
        <text>He argued that this was neither a coincidence, nor the result of the plankton adapting to the oceanic stoichiometry, but rather that phytoplankton adjust the N:P stoichiometry of the ocean to meet their requirements through nitrogen fixation, an idea supported by recent modelling studies.
</text>
        <annotation id="T1">
          <infon key="brat-id">T1</infon>
          <infon key="type">Variable</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="8" offset="447"/>
          <text>nitrogen</text>
        </annotation>
        <annotation id="T2">
          <infon key="brat-id">T2</infon>
          <infon key="type">Change</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="8" offset="456"/>
          <text>fixation</text>
        </annotation>
        <relation id="E1">
          <infon key="brat-id">E1</infon>
          <infon key="type">Change</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">event</infon>
